						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged. It records the gift of the village Eṭṭavāykkāl, excluding the lands therein which had been already granted to others as <hi rend="italic">sthānamānyam</hi>, to the temple of Tiruvēṅgaḍa-nāyaṉār as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam</hi> by Sōmappar under the orders of Kampaṇa-uḍaiyar. The actual ruler at the time was probably Bukka I. </p>						

						</summary>
